<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06106189 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06106189 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  GEORGIA; WOMAN; LAWSUIT; PAST; SPOUSE; MAGAZINE; PORNOGRAPHY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Susan Hudson's nude photograph didn't win the $5,000 prize from the men'smagazine that published it -- but it earned her a $225,000 judgment againsther ex-husband, who sent the picture to the magazine without her knowledge.;   A Cobb County, Ga., Superior Court jury, after deliberating for three hours,ruled that Jennings Gordon, 50, violated his ex-wife's privacy rights anddisgraced her when he sent the nude photograph to Gallery magazine in 1984without her knowledge or permission. The jury awarded her $225,000 in punitivedamages. She had asked for $5 million.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  NUDE PHOTO THAT WENT PUBLIC EARNS $225,000  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Gallery published the photograph in its monthly &quot;Girl Next Door AmateurErotic Photo Contest&quot; in October 1985 -- two weeks before Hudson was scheduledto remarry.;    &quot;This is the woman I love; I cannot explain, nor do I know whyI did these things,&quot; Gordon, a geologist, told the jury during the three-daytrial.;    Hudson, now 40, told the jury she posed nude for her husband'sphotographs more than 100 times. But she never meant for anyone but him to seethem.;    &quot;These photos were very, very private,&quot; Hudson told jurors. &quot;I didit in the trust of a marriage.&quot;;    Gordon &quot;is just a plain, mean, nasty,rotten person; a rich brat run amok,&quot; attorney Jeff Morrison said in closingarguments.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Cox News Service  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Atlanta  </CITY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910415  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  10A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  214  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday April 15, 